Concomitant medications included medroxyprogesterone acetate (DEPO PROVERA) taken from 07Apr2021 to an unspecified stop date; omeprazole (PRILOSEC); clarithromycin (CLARITIN); allopurinol (ELAVIL); magnesium; venlafaxine hydrochloride (EFFEXOR); warfarin sodium (COUMADIN); digoxin; metoprolol tartrate (LOPRESSOR); torsemide; acyclovir; aspirin; topiramate (TOPAMAX); insulin aspart (NOVOLOG); and atorvastatin. This case will be reassessed once additional information becomes available. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Caller received the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine on 09Feb2021. The second dose is scheduled for 02Mar2021 (lot number: EN6198) on left arm. She did ok for a few days after she received the Covid 19 vaccine. Caller started to experience some symptoms one week on 16Feb2021 after receiving the first dose of the vaccine which continued and are still persisting. She had imbalance problems, vertigo and dizziness. She guesses it affects her vestibular system. She had real bad spinning. She couldn't even sit up in bed she would just fall back into bed. She had to stay in bed. She reports it took a while to get in to see a doctor and to get therapy. Her doctor has diagnosed this as positional vertigo, but she said she never had it before. So she went to see a therapist and has been going to therapy for about 5 weeks. She started therapy on 04Mar2021. The therapist did the Epley's maneuver and that got rid of the spinning. But she still has bad balance. Her symptoms haven't gone away and she's had them for about 7 weeks. She's concerned and she thought therapy was helping and she was improving but yesterday morning she felt real bad again and she had to stay in bed again. She doesn't know why it comes and goes and it never goes away completely. She feels like her balance is on a rocking boat or a floor that's moving. And she can't make quick movements with her head or do any bending or turning. She's been going to therapy but she doesn't know why all of a sudden it comes back worse again. She can't really do normal things. She's seen where young people are having trouble. The Covid 19 vaccine must mess up her balance and must cause some kind of ear problems. Her primary care doctor suggested she go to therapy. She figured she would have some symptoms with the Covid 19 vaccine but her symptoms came later. It took her this long to realize her vertigo and balance problems might have come from the Covid 19 vaccine. But the problem is, she was looking at a website and she found that lots of people are having these side effects. Caller read some information online and noticed people have been reported imbalance and dizziness problems after receiving the vaccine. She thinks it was a mistake to get the Covid 19 vaccine. She read that some people are getting ringing in their ears. She reports that the ringing in her left ear was there prior to her receiving the Covid 19 vaccine and she doesn't think the ringing has changed any. When she had the real bad spinning the doctor thought it was positional vertigo and that was in her right ear. She thought about asking her doctor for an MRI but other people she read about said the MRI didn't show anything. She only went to her doctor's office. When she felt the worst she didn't feel like going to the hospital. She reports her husband had the same Covid 19 vaccine and he didn't have any trouble with it. Caller wants to know if these symptoms are associated with the vaccine. Also how long can the symptoms last since it been several weeks she's had them? The duration of protection against COVID -19 from the vaccine is unknown at the moment. For event vertigo positional, patient visit physician office. On 31Mar2021, a half an hour later, as the patient was driving home, the left side of her face started to feel hot and she kept putting her right hand on it to cool it off. The patient got a burning sensation that shot across the top of her left ear and nose. Once at home, she started to really feel weird on her face, and she had a burning sensation down the left side of her body. Her face felt strange for 1 hour and then declined. The patient went to bed at 09:30P.M. and she noticed numbness in her left leg. The next morning, the numbness in her left leg was much worse and she had numbness in her left arm down to fingers. States she called the doctor when they opened at 09:00 A.M. and they said to go to the ER right away because of all the numbness. The patient saw a neurologist on 05Apr2021, she has had more numbness on the right side. Clarified that her right foot feels numb intermittently along with the right side of her face. Her tongue has been numb on 31Mar2021, like a line across it, most of the time. The numbness ebbs and flows and where she feels it,  moves around. It is not as strong as a week ago but it moves around. No treatment was given in response to the events. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Sore Arm day after getting Vaccinated: Lasted a few days and faded away until there was no pain. Felt very Fatigued the day after getting the Vaccination: Lasted several days. But, got better with time.  Adverse event I wished to report: Seems this Vaccine might have, temporarily, hindered the effectiveness of a medication I take.  I'm on Amytriptyline 25mg, 2 a day at one time, for Postherpetic neuralgia on the right side of my face & right ear. This Amytriptyline medication has helped to cease all pain, including migraines, that I get from the Postherpetic neuralgia, and has also helped with the pain of pinched nerves in my back. Due to that, this medication has really helped improve my quality of life.  After getting the Vaccine, I went home and felt fine the first night. When waking up the next day, I found myself experiencing pain on the right side of my face and in my right ear. Thought this was odd as I took my medication the night before. But, as the day went on, it got a bit worse. That night i had trouble sleeping due to it. Then, the next day, I awoke with not only the pain at a level that it was before having treatment for it, but it also caused light sensitivity, migraines, and I could feel the right upper part of my jaw hurting as if teeth were aching that have been pulled years ago. I was also having vertigo when the ear pain got too bad.  This went on for several days and then faded away around the 20th of April 2021. Although I was confused as to why the Amytriptyline didn't seem to work as well on those days, I figured that it must be something to do with the vaccine effecting my nerves, or interacting with this medication. I did not seek medical advice for this reaction, as it went away. But just wanted to report it using this form. Thankyou.

The patient did not receive any other vaccine within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. The patient reported that she was calling about the Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine. She said she was a LVAD (Left Ventricular Assist Device) patient. She said the LVAD helped to pump blood in her heart, and the thickness of her blood was important for the LVAD pump to work.  She said after she got her first Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine on 24Mar2021 and her INR dropped drastically on 25Mar2021. She said she spent a week in the hospital to build her INR level back up until she could go home at an INR number that was safe. She said she talked with the doctor, who was the head of the heart failure unit at the hospital. She said both the doctor and her felt the Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine shot caused her INR problem. She said she now knows that she needs to bump up her warfarin dose if her INR were to drop after she gets the second Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine. She said she thought it was important that Pfizer know what happened to her. She reported that her pacemaker with defibrillator was triggered, and she was shocked 3 times, so she called the hospital and was told to go to the hospital's Emergency Room. She clarified she had her first COVID-19 Vaccine on 24Mar2021, and the next day (25Mar2021) her INR dropped to 1.4. She said her normal INR range was between 2-3. She said she went to the Emergency Room on 28Mar2021, and was admitted into the hospital. She said her INR was checked while she was in the Emergency Room, and her INR had dropped even further to .07 on 28Mar2021. She said when she was admitted to the hospital on 28Mar2021 and she was put on a slow IV drip of heparin as a bridge to warfarin. She said she eventually restarted warfarin on Wednesday, 31Mar2021, along with the IV Heparin drip. She said between the IV Heparin drip and the Warfarin, her INR reached 1.76 on 02Apr2021 and she was discharged from the hospital on 02Apr2021. She reported when she got home, she took a larger Warfarin dose for the first 3 days. She clarified she increased her Warfarin to 7.5 mg a day for 3 days, and used her current Warfarin prescription, adjusting the amount of Warfarin tablets she took. She said she then went back to her regular Warfarin dosing: 3.5 mg daily on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday, and 4 mg daily on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday and Sunday. She stated her Warfarin was dispensed in pharmacy bottles. She said she had 2 separate Warfarin doses she used at home, so she could adjust her Warfarin dosing, as needed, based on her INR levels. She reported she had her INR checked on Monday, 05Apr2021, and her INR had increased to 2.4. She said she was going later today (08Apr2021) to have her INR rechecked at the hospital's lab. She stated since she and her doctors were now aware of her INR situation after the first Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, her doctors will monitor her the day before she gets her second Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, and for several days afterwards. The event required a visit to emergency room. The outcome of the event was recovered on 01Apr2021.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Ankles started itching like he had mosquito bites / itching was out of control; Hives on ankles, hands, trunk, stomach, back, front, feet / hives all over; This is a spontaneous report received from a contactable consumer reporting on behalf of her husband. A 53 years old male patient received the first single dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE; lot ER2613, expiry date Jul2021) on 05Apr2021 at around 16:00, in left arm, for COVID-19 immunisation. No other vaccines were given within 4 weeks. Medical history included cold sores. Concomitant medication included valaciclovir hydrochloride (VALTREX) 1 g, 2 tablets when felt cold sore coming on, for cold sores. The patient took Valtrex just once in a while when he got cold sores, since probably 7-8 years ago. On 05Apr2021 at around 19:00 patient ankles started itching like he had mosquito bites. Hives started on the patient's ankles on 05Apr2021, then spread a little on his hands and a little on his trunk. Throughout the night of 05Apr2021, hives started appearing on his trunk, his stomach a little bit and some on his back. Over the course of 06Apr2021 to 07Apr2021, the hives spread to the patient's front, back, hands and feet. The patient worked most of 06Apr2021 and 07Apr2021 and the hives and the itching continued to get worse. The patient had more hives on 06Apr2021 and on 07Apr2021 he had hives all over. The patient's whole body was filled with hives. By 07Apr2021 night, the patient's itching was out of control and he couldn't hardly stand it. The events required physician office visit (urgent care for hives on 07Apr2021) and also emergency room during the night of 07Apr2021 and again on 08Apr2021 morning at 06:00. Caller reported that she and the patient just got back from the emergency room. The patient was starting to itch again. He lasted about 4 hours after getting home last night, 07Apr2021, and then went back to emergency room on 08Apr2021 morning. Nothing had really helped the patient's itching and hives. The medications took a little of the edge off of the patient's itching. They gave the patient an IV at the emergency room visit on 08Apr2021, but he was starting to itch again. The patient received a prescription for prednisone from urgent care (he had to take 60 mg  the first day, 60 mg the second day, and then taper down over 6 days). When the patient finally got the prescription for prednisone filled and the patient was finally able to take the prednisone, he was going crazy from the extreme itching. The patient hadn't eaten and ended up getting sick from the prednisone. First emergency room visit: the patient received a shot of diphenhydramine 50 mg at 11:33 PM and methylprednisolone sodium 125 mg at 11:36 PM on 07Apr2021. The emergency room gave the patient a prescription for doxepin 10 mg every night for 7 days to help the patient relax and so that he could sleep, but they were unable to have the prescription filled last night as the pharmacy was closed. The patient was given a dose of 10 mg of doxepin to go home with so that he could sleep. Second emergency room visit: the patient received diphenhydramine 50 mg injection at 7:54 AM, 20 mg of famotidine at 7:21 AM, 60 mg methylprednisolone at 7:19 AM, and a 500 mL bolus of sodium chloride 0.9% at 7:56 AM on 08Apr2021. The patient was sent home with prescriptions for hydroxyzine pamoate 50 mg, 1 capsule by mouth three times daily as needed for up to 5 days and famotidine 20 mg, 1 tablet by mouth twice daily for 5 days. Hydroxyzine, famotidine, diphenhydramine, methylprednisolone and doxepin had not really helped the patient's hives and itching. The patient was still trying to recover at the time of report.  No follow up attempts are possible. No further information is expected.

I let the EMT's know and the asked me questions to make sure I could breath ok and wasn't going into anaphylactic shock (I could breath fine). After 30 min I left and threw up on my way home and 3-4 more times after I got home. I took ibuprofen for my headache and took a nap, an hour or so later I woke up and had hives all over my arms and some on my neck and back. I called the advice nurse on my insurance card and she directed me to Teledoc (they do video/phone app's) to make a Dr. appointment. I made my app for 4/23/21. Even though my hives were pretty much all cleared up by then(2 days later) I still wanted to ask the Dr. If I should get the second shot or look into another vaccine. He told me to not get the second Pfizer dose and it was up to me if I wanted to get another one like the Moderna or J&J one. He said I was 50-60% immune instead of the full 95% and that was better than nothing. I'm glad I got the vaccine but will not be getting any more in the future.

Ethnicity information was available. Race information was available.
CUR_ILL: Familial Mediterranean fever (Familial Mediterranean Fever (FMF) but do not present active symptoms (Genetic asymptomatic carrier for Familial Mediterranean Fever)); Iodine allergy (Allergies to medications, food, or other products: Iodine); Migraine

I started feeling like I was getting my period even before I got my second shot. On the one hand, maybe I was and it was just a coincidence. I had the typical brain fog, muscle and overall body fatigue. Nothing horrible, but it was there. The second shot itself was no big deal and I went about my day no problem afterward. I was just surprised when I started menstruating given that I haven't actually bled in more than a year because I am on the Mirena IUD (inserted in 2018). Period symptoms like tender breasts and being foggy heads or tired for a day is one thing, an actual period is another. I haven't even had spotting in at least a year, probably two. I had active (light) bleeding for 2 or 3 days. I am now two and a half weeks post my second shot and my breasts are as tender as if I am getting my period imminently, which doesn't make sense at all given the timing. I had the most painful mammogram I have ever experienced in my life on Friday (April 23) though the results were clear. Other than that, and since the moment I got my shot,  I have felt perfectly fine. Maybe a little tired and hungover feeling the day immediately after the shot, but nothing more.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin D (1000IUs) daily Sertraline (50mg) daily Folic Acid (1mg) daily Skipped for day of shot, but typically also take prednisone (2mg daily), methotrexate (15mg every week), leucovorin (10mg every week), and cimzia (200mg every 3 weeks)

Patient received vaccine in left arm (deltoid). Was in post vaccination observation area. About 5 minutes after the injection, while sitting in the observation chairs, the patient fainted and hit his head on the floor. Pharmacist and patient's father got him back up into the chair. Patient quickly regained consciousness, but felt nauseous and warm. Patient was given a little water. But could carry-on a conversation.  Patient vomited a little into a trash can. About 10 additional minutes went by. Patient was able to get up out of the chair and walk out of the facility with the help of his family. Patient had a little bit of bump on head where he had struck the floor, no bleeding occurred. No additional medical assistance was contacted at that time by the facility, family, or the pharmacist. Pharmacist called the patient several hours to after to see how he was doing, but did not get a response. The pharmacist left a voicemail. It is unknown to the pharmacist whether or not the family decided it was necessary to get medical follow-up or not after the incident.

Fever of 99.7 to 100.2; body chills with fever; body aches; headache. Treatment was Tylenol in the first 24 hours and ibuprofen after the first 24 hours. Treatment had a small effect on symptoms; however it did not totally take them away.

The Patient has an anaphylactic history to an oral pain medication she didn't know the name of, food allergies, and to the flu vaccine (with eggs). She has gotten the flu shot without eggs and been fine. The administering RN asked the med led to further assess. We discussed that she is at a higher risk for anaphylaxis than most people given her allergy history. She said that she was not Allergic to any component of the covid 19 vaccine when shown the list, and this was double checked. We discussed that if she gets the vaccine and has a reaction, she will need emergency room treatment and that she may want to consider being vaccinated at a hospital where they have more resources. However, given she did have known anaphylaxis to a component of the vaccine we will give it to her if she so chooses. It was explained that if she gets the vaccine, we will monitor her for 45 minutes, and if she has a reaction, she will be treated and sent to the E.R. She verbalized consenting to getting the vaccine after being thoroughly educated.  She was vaccinated at 1337 with 0.5 ml of Moderna Vaccine in the left deltoid. I was not present upon the administration. I was informed shortly after administration that she had cold sweaty palms and felt a little lightheaded. She was placed in a wheelchair and taken to a private observation tent to be further assessed. Initially in the tent she was not showing alarming signs of anaphylaxis and appeared stable. She had clear lung sounds and her oxygen level was 99% with no respiratory distress or airway compromise. At 1405 she felt her lips and throat get tingly and slightly bigger, although upon assessment they did not appear swollen. She was fasting and refused to swallow water or Benadryl when offered. She was able to swallow her spit with no issues. We explained to her that we are going to keep monitoring her, but if things change at all we are going to have to call 911 and administer epinephrine. She kept saying she is fine and that she did not want it and that her boyfriend would take her home. Currently her VS were BP 94/70, HR 72, O2 99%, RR 22. She was rubbing her back and her lungs were clear.  At 1410 her bp was 90/62, HR 74, o2 98% and RR 24. Again, she was rubbing her back. Her lungs sounded clear. At 1415 her BP was 84/60, HR 80, O2 93%, and RR rate of 30. She had small expiratory wheezes when listening to her breath sounds. She appeared to be in respiratory distress as she was coughing and rubbing her chest. She stated her chest felt back, neck, and chest felt tight. She still stated she was fine, and she did not have insurance. She was informed that this was a life-threatening emergency  At this time 911 was called as it was determined she was having an anaphylactic reaction needing epinephrine. Her Emergency contact was notified as he was on the phone with her. At 1417 0.3 mg of epinephrine was administered into the left deltoid, which is where I was informed, she had received the vaccine. At 1420 her VS read 118/74, HR 122, O2 99%. Her respiratory distress appeared to be improving, and her VS improving. She stated she felt better, and she wanted to go home, but per policy she was taken to EMS in a wheelchair. She was handed off to EMS around 225 and verbal report was given. She was transferred to her emergency contact was present for transfer and filled in of the events.
HISTORY: Rn found an inhaler and patient said she has Asthma Unsure of other comorbidities as not assessed
ALLERGIES: Flu shot with eggs anaphylaxis, vaccines without eggs are fine multiple foods (pt didn't state what ones) Anaphylaxis Oral pain medication anaphylaxis

I have had Paroxysmal AFib since 2012 and had an ablation in 2016.  It cured the Afib about 90-95 percent, but I still get intermittent episodes, ALWAYS brought on by some catalyst, (alcohol, sexual relations, drinking a cold beverage, exercise).  However, appr. two weeks after the vaccine, I began getting random bouts of Afib, longer in episodes, but shorter in duration.  Since the vaccine, I have had appr. 12+ episodes of Afib, occurring at various times, even at rest.  Since the ablation, I got about 12 episodes per year, now it's been 12 episodes in 2 months.  Sometimes, I'll get several episodes a day, at random times for no reason.  This has been totally opposite of what I was experiencing pre-vaccine.  What concerns me is that the episodes are random and there are not catalysts to bring them on.

Prior medical history included COVID disease in January, 2021. Due to his history, he was vaccinated next to our ambulance with physician and EMS team in attendance. Approximately 5 minutes after vaccination, recipient began complaining of dryness of the throat and feeling a lump in his throat without any compromise in breathing. Approximately 9 minutes post vaccination, he complained of a progression of his swallowing symptoms, swelling and pressure feeling (periorbital and in the malar area) of the face. He did not complain of dyspnea. Due to his symptoms, he was administered 0.3 mL of epinephrine IM at 10:39, followed by diphenhydramine 50 mg IM approximately 1-2 minutes later. Symptoms seemed to remain static, with treatment, with the exception of post-epinephrine shakiness and complaints of tingling of his feet. I recieved my first Moderna COVID vaccine on January 11, 2021 at 10:28 AM. I received my second dose vaccine on February 8, 2021 at 10:33 AM. Both injections were given at Cancer Center's Covid vaccine clinic. I began developing all-over itching and rash soon after the second vaccine and had a Teladoc appointment with Dr. on February 10th. He prescribed predniSONE 1 mg oral tablet and it basically did nothing. I then had another Teladoc appointment on Feburary 14th with Dr. and he prescribed predniSONE 20 mg oral tablet and the visit was short and I didn't feel heard and I decided to have a second opinion before taking more steroids. I then saw a Nurse Practitioner on 2/15/21 and she prescribed cephALEXin (Keflex) and methylPREDNISolone (Medrol Dosepack) and I began taking these prescriptions and the rash was still itchy but didn't seem to spread as much while I was on the steroid. As soon as I stopped the steroid, the intense itching returned and started spreading more. The rash and itching got even more intense, so I consulted another Teladoc physician and this time he was a dermatologist, he prescribed me a 21 day course of high dose steroids. This treatment made the itching subside and I didn't notice a rash while I was on the higher doses of the steroid but the itching and rash returned as I went to lower doses of the steroid as I was tapering and it completely returned even worse as soon as I was off of the steroid and I tried to just deal with it but it got worse as time went on. I then made an appointment with NP on March 22, and she took a skin biopsy of one of my spots and prescribed me Triamcinolone Acetonide cream to use all over my body to stop the itching. The biopsy results came back on March 30th and the results said it was a possible drug reaction/hypersensitivity reaction. The only thing new for me this entire time has been the Moderna Vaccine. I have not started any new drugs or changed anything else in my life that would cause this response. I am still itchy all over and using the topical cream prescribed. The only other treatment option she offered was a light therapy that she said could help but I cannot afford at this time.
LAB_DATA: Skin Biopsy of a spot- March 22, 2021 with Nurse Practitioner.
PRIOR_VAX: First Covid vaccine on January 11, 2021. Mild itching in localized place (right arm- where vaccine was administered).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My mensural cycle began the same day that I received the vaccine. My period was extended to last a total of two weeks. At the injection site, a large red welt appeared and was consistently present for a total of two weeks. Being in the sun, irritated the welt and would turn it bright red and itchy.  The welt would come and go for an entire month following the injection. For the first five days following the injection, my left middle finger acted as if it was jammed on and off. The finger ached and hurt and I was unable to bend said finger.  I had a low grade fever for a couple days following the injection.   One month after the injection, I formed an outer ear infection in my left ear and minor scrapes were not healing as they did in the past. Scrapes and cuts began taking weeks to heal instead of days. The ear infection lasted one week before I asked for antibiotic drops. The day that I received antibiotics, my ear infection spread to the right ear, and lasted another week. Both ear infections lasted approximately one week each. Also a month after my injection, my facial acne increased substantially and I began feeling lethargic with light throat irritations such as coughing and flem.   Due to these reactions to the first Moderna injection, I elected to not receive the second injection.   Five weeks after my injection, on 23 Apr 21, I received my TDAP booster and PPV23, one in each arm. I have never had reactions to vaccines prior to the Moderna injection; but now, for the first two days after the booster injections, I could not raise my arms due to severe pain and muscle aches at the injection sites. I felt weak and lethargic as well as experienced lightheadedness and rushes of blood pressure changes on 24 Apr 21. Currently on 25 Apr 21, I am still experiencing moderate injection site pains and feel lethargic.
HISTORY: Fibromyalgia, PTSD, insomnia, Raynaud's syndrome, visual distortions of shape and size, bilateral tinnitus, neck and back pains, and systemic reactions to allergy immunotherapy injections.

On April 16th I was weight training when my R arm became suddenly painful and heavy feeling.  A few hours later I noticed my arm had gotten very swollen and blue.  I went to urgent care and was sent for an US.  It showed a large clot in my internal jugular vein as well as clots in my R subclavian, axillary, brachial, proximal cephalic, and proximal basilic veins.  They sent me to ER and did a CT and also found a small PE in my L lower lobe pulmonary artery.  Currently I am on enoxaparin and very limited in use of my R arm.  The cause of my clots remains unknown.  I am waiting on blood tests to see if I have any genetic factors.  It seems unlikely that this is tied to the vaccination but I wanted to report in case there end up being similar cases.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 24-36 hours after receiving the vaccine I experienced pain/burning on my labia (the outside, not inside). After inspecting it myself I realized I had multiple lesions 2 days post vax. I saw a nurse practitioner and I went on anti virals prescribed by a local woman?s clinic for suspected herpes which cleared things up within the 10 day regimen. They immediately did a swab of the area for suspected herpes simplex which was negative. I have since done 4+ herpes simplex 1 and 2 tests (blood and swab) and all have been negative. I have also done HIV, RPR, chlamydia, gonorrhea, and auto immune blood tests (and more) and all results have been negative. The issue is now cleared but my PCP wanted to find the root cause of the issue and potential underlying condition.   I have a history of shingles on my back/shoulder and the pain/lesions appeared similar in nature but presented on both sides of my labia in this situation (though much more on one side than the other). My last major outbreak on my back/shoulder was in 2010-2011. This was the only outbreak in which lesions appeared though I sometimes feel the area tingle/tense up when under stress or sick.   In addition to the lesions, I had typical flu like symptoms after the vaccine that began about 8 hours after and lasted for 2-3 days.
LAB_DATA: Bloodwork and swabs for herpes simplex, hiv, syphillus, gonorrhea, chlamydia, auto immune disease indicators, and more. All testes conducted were negative.

Received  the vaccine at 10:;15 am on 4/14/2021 and had fatigue, slight chills, and a sore arm.  By 4/16/2021 I felt normal until approx. 10pm when my right ear blocked up and I lost hearing in my right ear.  On 4/17/2021 I treated it as a congestion issue with neti pot and decongestions but the ear remained blocked.  After sleeping for approx 1 hour on 4/17/2021 I woke up at approx. 11pm with severe vertigo and nausea and vomited consistently for approx 1 hour.  I could not get off of the floor and the right side of my face was fixated to the floor.  Paramedics were called and I was taken to the ER where I was treated with anti-nausea medications and valium to reduce vertigo.  A non contrast CT, blood panel, and stroke assessment were all normal with no sign of ear infection.  I was release from the hospital at 10am on 4/19/2021.    On 4/21/2021 I saw an ENT who performed a hearing exam revealing my right ear is completely deaf with normal left ear function.  The ENT prescribed prednisone 10mg (63 tablets over 10 days).   As of today (4/25/2021) I no longer have vertigo and nausea, but I still have no hearing in my right ear and have significant vestibular challenges and cannot walk safely unassisted without getting dizzy.
LAB_DATA: Non contrast CT - normal with no indication of stroke (4/17/2021) CBC - normal (4/17/2021) ED Stroke Assessment Order Set - normal (4/17/2021) Dix-Hallpike - negative for BPPV for both sides (4/21/2021) Audiogram - "profound" hearing loss in right ear (4/21/2021)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: When I  received my second dose of Moderna on 4/20 and mentioned the side effects I received from the first shot, the person administering the shot said I should report it to the cdc. On the night of my first shot (3/23) I had a skin reaction that was VERY itchy, raised, red, hot, and burned when I itched it. The area spread and then shrank but remained localized to the area where I received the vaccine.  This started the day of the first shot and lasted for a week. It started to go down and then a week after I received the shot, I had another skin reaction except this time it grew to the size of my palm. It was itchy, raised, hot, and red. From what I read online, it seems like I had ?covid arm?. I tried calling my health care provider one morning and they offered me a virtual appointment for the early evening of the following day. I felt like they didn?t think it was serious since they were going to have me wait 30+ hours to see someone so I just took Benadryl instead. This helped with the itching, which was the most annoying part. I actually still have a mark on my left arm today, more than a month after the first shot, so the woman advised I get my second shot in my right arm. It seems like I had an initial reaction the vaccine that lasted about a week and then got the covid arm. My arm was itchy and raised for about 3 weeks. I took pictures of my arm a couple of times a day for the first two and a half weeks to document the progression.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 4/14/2021  Two weeks after the 2nd Covid-19 vaccine,,about 11 PM.  patient, developed a sudden numbness in his right are, hand & right side of the face.  He had no sensation and could not feel anything.  He immediately was taken to the emergency room at Hospital.  They began testing and suspected a blood clot.  They administered blood thinners, TPA by injection into the port, performed many tests including Ct scan, chest Xray, blood tests, EKG etc.  He was being monitored & hooked up to various scanners.  They decided to move him by Ambulance to the ICU Unit at Medical Center .  He was in the neurology emergency room there for several hours & then moved the Neurology ICU. They kept him there, doing various testing, until Friday 4/16/2021 When they moved him to a regular Neurology floor.  Staff neurologists continued to monitor his condition.  On Saturday, 4/6/2021, an MRI showed a small blood clot in the Thalamus of the brain, which they believe caused the lack of sensation  on the right arm, hand & face.    He was discharged & went home on Monday 4/18/2021.  New medication was prescribed, Physical therapy and was told to make an appointment with a Neurologist.  On Thursday, 4/22/2021 patient had an appointment with his Cardiologist, Dr. the Dr gave him an examination & told him to proceed with the neurologist, etc.  Patient has an appointment at PT in on Wed. April 28, 2021.  He is waiting for an appointment with Dr. Neurologist at Neurology Group

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt was in observation area, went to operations table and told them she felt faint. Pt then passed out onto carpet. Onsite EMTs and charge nurse were called. Pt revived after 15-20 sec, was able to respond to questions. Pulse was taken - 62 bpm. Pt stated she had a history of passing out when receiving a needlestick but it had not happened in past two years. Pt was assisted to w/c and taken to observation area outside ballroom. VS were taken and were WNL (BP 120/70, HR 61, SpO2 99% RA, RR 16). Pt asked for water, stated she was feeling better. EMTs advised pt she could be transported to ED for further eval - pt refused. Pt denied any pain or soreness. After 15 min, VS were taken again, and again were WNL (BP 106/76, RR 16, HR 75 bpm, SpO2 99% RA). Pt left shortly after 2nd VS eval, stated she "felt fine," was advised to seek emergent help if sx resume, esp to pull over and call emergency number if she felt dizzy again while driving home. Pt stated understanding.

Patient warned us before his covid vaccine that he has a severe needle phobia and has fainted after vaccines.  I gave him his immunization quickly and he did well.  He stood up and watched as I immunized his wife.  He said he was feeling okay afterwards so both him and his wife left the immunization room.  Shortly after leaving he must have started getting dizzy, because next thing I hear is that there is an unconscious man in the waiting room.  He is sitting in a chair with his head back unresponsive.  His wife if rubbing his arms and lightly slapping his face.  He comes to, and we decide to move him to the room that the clinic uses (we have a walk in clinic staffed with a NP).  He lays on the floor, and within a minute he proceds to vomit approximately 4 times.  He also lost control of his bladder.  He was pale with cold and clammy skin.  we moved him so we could put his feet up on a chair and allowed him to rest.  Someone went to get him an ice pack to put on his head and chest.  His blood pressure was low (90/50ish).   He still was not feeling better after 30 minutes so we called the ambulance.  He did not want to go to the hospital so the paramedics monitored him.  his blood pressure slowly started going up and normalizing, and he left with his wife.
PRIOR_VAX: needle phobia.  has had dizziness/fainting after immunizations in past

I got the shot at around 4 in the afternoon and after sitting in the waiting area for around 15 minutes I was allowed to leave. When I left I only had a slight headache, but nothing that seemed very noticeable. I felt a tad woozy but it was nothing serious so I went on with my day and went to my sports practice for an hour and a half. After I got home and had eaten, I was working and started to feel the effects. It started with an increasingly worse headache at around 9 and as the night went on it got worse and I constantly needed to lie down. My arm had started to feel sore but it was nothing much. I thought I could sleep it off but woke up feeling horrible. My stomach could not hold any food down and my headache had become really bad. About two hours after my second shot, I started feeling tingling in my legs.  Within half an hour, the tingling spread to my arms and face and my lips and tongue started to swell and my throat felt like it was closing.  I called 911, and they gave me an epipen, shot of steroids, and a shot of benadryl and said I went into anaphylaxis shock.  I was released from the hospital Friday night, but on Monday night I had another (milder) allergic reaction and the following day began to have shortness of breath.  I went to my doctor's on Tuesday, who prescribed me steroids and histamine blockers.  I began taking them but on Wednesday my difficulty breathing increased and it got to the point where I had difficultly swallowing and couldn't eat so I went to the ER again.  I have had some sort of rash and hives every day since my second shot, which my doctor says is a continuing allergic reaction from the shot.  I am going to see an allergist, but I have no history of allergies or allergic reactions to vaccines.
LAB_DATA: ER hospital on Friday, April 16 - lots of drugs and tests Tuesday, April 20, visit to primary doctor, of Health facility, who prescribed me steroids, inhaler, and histamine blockers Wednesday, April 21, another trip to  ER, doctors just gave me adavin

Patient received first dose of Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine on 4/25/2021 at 2:50pm. Patient was in observation area chair 1 and technician noticed she was pale in color and patient waved technician over to her.  Technician went to her and then alerted Pharmacist that patient was feeling light headed and was pale.  I went to patient and asked her how she was feeling and if she was having any trouble breathing. Patient was starting to slouch in her chair and I asked her if I could lower her to the ground.  At that time, she passed out and was unresponsive.  I lowered her to the floor and supported her head with my hand.  She was unresponsive for about 5-10 seconds but then her eyes popped open wide and she made a large gasping breath.  She was very disoriented and asked what happened.  As I talked to her and asked her questions, she became oriented with her surroundings and was able to verbally communicate with me how she was feeling.  Patient was reporting tingling in hands, heart racing, and was visually shaky.  I asked her if she wanted me to call EMS and she responded yes.  At this time, patient was beyond the 15 minutes post observation waiting period.   Technician called emergency number, I stayed on the ground with the patient and continued to assess her symptoms and her breathing.  The color in her face resumed to normal and she was able to use her cell phone to contact her father.  While sitting on the ground with her, she reported she was beginning to feel better, but was still feeling weird in her head.  At that time, EMS arrived and took over.

Patient checked in for her vaccination appointment on Sunday 04/25/21 at approximately 03:50 pm. After speaking with the pharmacist she confirmed that she did not have any prior history of any allergies to any medications. She mentioned that she had a history of anxiety and was nervous about receiving the vaccination. She received her first dose of the Moderna Covid19 vaccine at between approximately 03:55 - 04:05 pm. She then went to the designated observation area. Before completing her observation period, the patient got up and walked to the pharmacy at which point she fainted and was lying on the floor in a supine position. The pharmacy staff was alerted and checked on the patient. The manager in charge was notified and came to the pharmacy. The patient was checked on for responsiveness and she was alert and responsive. She asked for her father who was in the store at the time and she also asked for some water. She stood up with some assistance and sat down in an observation chair. Her father came over and the technician provided the patient some water. The patient stayed an additional 15 minutes in her chair speaking to her father and drinking her water.  After which, she got up and left with her father.
HISTORY: Patient reported she has a history of anxiety.
ALLERGIES: Patient answered "No" to immunization consent form question #6 Do you have any allergies to medications, food, or any vaccine?

I received the 2nd dose of Pfizer Wednesday. Thursday I experienced many of the typical side effects: overwhelming exhaustion, pain in the injection arm, dizziness, slight muscle aches and on/off chills without a fever. By Friday, I woke up feeling almost normal. I ran around 11am Friday on my home treadmill and felt fine. Saturday we went for a hike and I felt fine. That afternoon I was tired but nothing terrible. Today, Sunday, I went for a run outside on a route I do often. I went a slow, comfortable pace. I felt good. Then I got to the final hill at the end and felt like something was in my throat, itching it and I needed to cough. I tried to cough lightly at first but it didn't help. I drank from my hydration pack and coughed more deeply. I felt my vision go out a bit and stopped completely. Then suddenly it felt like my lung collapsed and I couldn't breathe. It sounded like I had croup, barely breathing through a wheeze. I was struggling for any oxygen at all, like a clogged straw. I was terrified. It lasted about 20 seconds and then started to ease up.  I was able to get more and more oxygen. It still felt like cobwebs on my lungs,  a tight/heavy feeling for the next 20 minutes or so and then back to normal. I have never experienced something like this before. It was downright terrifying.

I woke up at 3 am Friday with cold sweats and body aches. Took 1000 mg Tylenol. Woke up again at 10:30 am to a fever still and this odd extremity feeling. Felt like I had a compression body suit on and weight of 50 pounds around my arms and legs, Mild shortness of breath. I felt like I was swollen but did not see any. I called my PCP and vaccine line and both nurses said go to the ER. I went to the ER they ran tests. The time of the ER I started getting leg cramping and spasming. Those symptoms continued to the weekend. On Sunday the weight and swelling feeling went away. I still had bad muscle cramping and swelling. I did telehealth on Tuesday with PCP and was given muscle relaxer which helped some throughout the rest of the week. Thursday night I have a temp pf 99.6 and went up to 100.6 on Friday morning. On Friday I became shortness of breath and fatigued. It became difficult to go up and down stairs or walking about 20 ft without difficulty breathing. I now have a lower right leg muscle twitch/spasm that comes and goes. I switched to a different PCP, he ran more blood work on Wednesday 4/21. And discussed the next steps for treatment and monitoring.
LAB_DATA: Xrays and lab work have been done results have been with in normal limits

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient began experiencing pain and difficulty walking on Tuesday, March 23. Later that afternoon she was taken to an Urgent care, who sent her to the ER for evaluation. She was diagnosed with a very large blood clot in her leg, spanning from just above the knee to her groin area. They admitted her and began treating her with blood thinners.  While undergoing that treatment, her heart stopped 3 times and she had to be resuscitated. They discovered a pulmonary embolism.  While removing a large clot from her lungs, the doctor found that her lungs were riddled with hundreds of tiny blood clots. They also said that she was bleeding internally, very heavily, from an unknown location. In all, they gave her 20 units of blood, and none of it stayed in her veins. The doctor said it seemed to just disintegrate.  At that point, her brain and organs had begun shutting down and family made the decision to remove her from life support. She passed away Thursday evening, March 25, 2021.

The vaccine was given on 4-23-2021 at about 11:30 AM at the Pharmacy. I came home and worked on my computer for about an hour. By 2 PM that day, I had the typical reactions expected of constant chills, fatigue, and soreness at the injection site of my left arm. I took a nap and covered up under many blankets. I drank lots of fluids to help. By 10 PM, I already felt lots of severe body aches and stiffness. Before midnight I started having chest pain. The chest pain continued all night making it difficult to sleep. I woke up completely around 7 AM on 4-24-2021 still feeling all body aches with difficulty moving, continued intensifying chest pain with palpitations, and now also felt nausea. I only ate a piece of fruit. I went with my family to our kid?s soccer games, but I was completely fatigued. I came home and took a nap, but felt chilled, the chest pain continuing, and soreness. When I woke up things were feeling even worse with the chest pain. They started to feel like a real heaviness on my chest, almost as if someone was sitting on me. I also felt a huge tightness the length of my sternum. I had palpitations. I started also having shortness of breath and could not walk up and down my stairs (which is never otherwise a problem).  I was very hot and sweating through my clothese. My sister took me to the ER because the pain became intolerable. I went to the Clinic, Hospital ER for the chest pain (lot so heaviness and tightness in the sternum) and shortness of breath. My blood pressure was really high in the 140s/90s. I was in a lot of pain. I had a temperature. They did an EKG immediately that showed PVCs and a slight pause. Then, I had an XRay of the chest and lots of bloodwork. They did give me fluids and pain medication. The bloodwork had elevated d-dimer and low potassium levels, so they did a CAT scan with contrast to rule out a clot. It showed no clot, but had very enlarged lymph nodes on the left. They believed all of this response and chest pain was due to my 2nd dose of Moderna's COVID 19 vaccine. I am still not completely recovered. I am feeling ill and chest pain with tightness, but at home now. I go back to my cardiologist for a repeat EKG and repeat bloodwork this week.
LAB_DATA: 4-24-2021: EKG - PVC and pause  Bloodwork included D-dimer ( high), HCG, ProBPN N-terminal, TNT High Sensitivity test 1, CBC + AUTO DIFF , COMPREHENSIVE METABOLIC PANEL (Low Potassium / Hypokalemia),  TNT High Sensitivity test 2  IV attempts 4 plus IV fluids, Toradol   Other medications given: Tylenol and Potassium   XR CHEST 1V FRONTAL - no acute findings  CT CHEST W IVCON PE ( No PE, but Mildly enlarged left axillary lymph nodes)  Clinical Impression at ER: Adverse reaction to COVID-19 vaccine
OTHER_MEDS: Metoprolol 75 mg daily, Rosuvastatin 5mg daily, Spironolactone 12.5 mg daily
HISTORY: Migraines (since 2014), Essential Hypertension (Controlled on medication), Pure Hypercholesterolemia (Controlled on medication), Obesity, Vitamin D deficiency
ALLERGIES: Erythromycin, Latex, Nickel, Adhesives, Ragweed, Dust Mites, Insects - Bees, Cockroaches, Strawberries, Bananas, Polluck fish

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the moderna vaccine on 02/23/2021 1st dose. My LMP was 02/03/2021. On 3/5/2021, I took a pregnancy test due to nausea and it was positive. I was super concerned due to getting the covid vaccine around the time of ovulation and so I contacted my FNP  and started getting serial Hcgs due to right side pelvic pain which was confirmed to be a hemorrhagic corpus luteal cyst.  A couple of weeks later, My 4th Pregnancy was confirmed via trans vaginal ultrasound  with a strong heart beat on 03/30/2021 and a gestational age of 7 weeks exactly and  a due date of 11/16/2021.   I decided not to get the 2nd dose of the vaccination due to concerns of miscarrying in the first trimester and limited studies on covid vaccine and it?s safety despite having 3 healthy children and zero miscarriages in the past.  On to my next appt on 04/19/2021, the fetus should alreayd measure at 10 weeks. Without having any abdominal pain, bleeding, or spotting, the baby stopped growing and measured at 7 weeks and 5 days with no heartbeat. Again, I had no symptoms of miscarrying at all.  We decided for a d&c and sent the fetal tissue for genetic testing. My d&c was performed on 04/22/2021 at 12pm.  We are currently waiting for genetic testing results at this time.
LAB_DATA: 04/22/2021 CBC, CMP, PTT as pre op labs for d&c.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Possible COVID Vaccine Reaction  Introduction I am writing this because I think all of the issues described under the ?Current Situation? section may somehow be tied to an adverse reaction to my second COVID shot.  Until today, I had thought they were separate incidents with no common thread.  I now can see the possibility that they may be related.  I am asking for competent and engaged medical help to determine whether this is so, and if not, what the causes are for my issues.  I will give a brief medical history to give some current perspective.  Health History Current Vital Statistics ? Age: 66, Gender: Male, Height: 6?3?, Weight: 245  Hemorrhoidectomy ? In 1999 I had a hemorrhoidectomy to stop episodes of severe bleeding.  Heart Attack ? In August 2000 I had a heart attack, diagnosed as unstable angina, while on vacation.  They did further tests, found blockages and inserted stents in two arteries.  I was sent home with instructions to contact a cardiologist.  AICD ? After returning home, my new cardiologist did further tests and found evidence of ventricular tachycardia.  I was sent to a specialist who did an electrophysiology study and immediately implanted an AICD.  I have had it replace twice, with the latest one in April 2012.  It has never gone off.  There are close to five years left on my current battery.  Knee Replacement ? In January 2015 I had a total knee replacement of my right knee.  That was a result of several injuries and four surgeries, which left the knee without cartilage.  The knee replacement has worked flawlessly, and I am able to pursue athletics, especially playing tennis, without limitation.   Current Situation February 23 ? Received my first shot of the Moderna vaccine in my right arm.  Other than minor soreness around the injection site, I had no other reaction.  March 29 ? Received the second shot of the Moderna vaccine in my right arm.  Again, there was minor soreness around the injection site.  April 2 ? Had major pain in my tightness in my chest and major pain starting in my left shoulder and radiating down my left arm.  It caused significant discomfort, and I was awake a large part of the night deciding whether I need to call 911 for a possible heart attack.  I decided against that and instead went to urgent care in the morning (April 3).  My EKG was normal, my blood pressure was elevated (158/96 sitting, 157/91 standing).  Doctor could find nothing to suggest heart attack.  Prescribed a course of Prednisone for the shoulder/arm pain.  Had blood work ordered, which all came back normal.  April 5 ? Played doubles tennis as usual.  Noticed some weakness in my left shoulder and arm but played through it successfully.  The pain level was very low.  April 10 ? Played doubles tennis again.  From the first ball I hit I was aware of major weakness in my shoulder and arm.  They had no power at all, and I was almost unable to get my serve over the net.  I played through it again and played very poorly.  The interesting thing was that the pain and weakness did not worsen during the play or afterwards.  The pain remained after I had finished playing.  April 11 ? Chatted with the athletic trainer while I was officiating their women?s tennis match to look for clues as to what might be wrong.  He suggested in may be a shoulder impingement.  April 15 ? Had a phone consult with my primary care doctor.  I suggested the possibility of the shoulder impingement and he was willing to start there since this was a phone visit.  He referred me to orthopedics and physical therapy and prescribed meloxicam for pain.  The pain has continued unabated during this time.  April 21 ? Pain level was very high to the point where I was unable to work.  Went home and slept most of the day.  Meloxicam was not having much impact on the pain compared to my usual regimen of both acetaminophen and ibuprofen (which I had stopped using when I was taking the meloxicam).  After this I stopped the meloxicam and went back to the other drugs as required.  I had an initial visit with the physical therapist that afternoon.  She did not find anything which would suggest a rotator cuff or labrum injury.  Range of motion was normal.  She noted weakness in my left side compared to my right, which is unusual since I am left-handed.  She gave me three exercises to do daily.  April 23 ? Pain had been back to a more tolerable level.  I had a COVID test in the morning for a treadmill test I have next week, and also got an x-ray of my shoulder as requested by my primary care doctor.  After I went to bed, I had an incident of severe incident of chills which left me freezing and short of breath even with sweats on under my bed covers.  I called my wife in to check my vitals.  My blood pressure was a bit higher than normal but not critical.  My blood oxygen was 98 and my pulse was 70.  My temperature was 99.7 with an oral thermometer.  We called the after-hours nurse hotline and spoke with a nurse.  By that time, it had been about 30 minutes of chills and they were subsiding.  She said she would have a doctor call in the next couple of hours.  The doctor called back, and after going over everything, said to come in if the symptoms reoccurred.  Thankfully they did not.  All the while I am still having the pain in my left shoulder and arm.  April 24 ? Again, slept most of the day due to being worn out from the previous night issues and lack of sleep.  No change in the pain and discomfort.
OTHER_MEDS: metoprolol, allopurinol, atorvastatin, fexofenadine, esomeprazole, aspirin
HISTORY: Heart attack (2000), AICD (2001), Knee replacement (2015), GERD, sinus allergies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second dose of Pfizer around 3pm on Sunday, April 4 2021. By about midnight, I had a fever and the fever/headache and exhaustion persisted throughout Monday. I did not take any medicine. By Tuesday morning, my fever broke, but I developed a large 6 inch rash under my left armpit (my second shot was in my right arm as I am left handed). By Tuesday afternoon, I had developed a bad cough. Given that I work remotely, and had only been to a grocery store (double masked) with my mother a few days prior to the second dose, I assumed the cough was a result of the second dose. My cough become worse, and by Wednesday it sounded like bronchitis so I went to my doctor. She believed that it was a bronchitis cough, had me tested for viral infections, and put me on a variety of medications from antibiotics to steroids and inhalers. I tested negative for all the respiratory illnesses I was tested for, as well as COVID-19. The medications did not seem to help, and my doctor added another inhaler and medication to the mix. After about 2 weeks of medications and no improvements, my doctor had me get a chest X-ray to make sure I didn?t have pneumonia or any other obstruction in my lungs. I also stopped all medication on Tuesday, April 20. My chest X-ray came back clear later that week, and I decided to just stay off all medications and hope that my body would self heal, since this seemed to be a self created bronchitis, as my parents did not get sick. Finally, after 2 weeks and 4 days, my cough has improved significantly to the point where I can now talk almost normally, without going into coughing spasms and feeling as though it was difficult to breathe.
LAB_DATA: Viral respiratory panel - 4/7/2021, all negative  Chest X-ray - 4/19/2021, was completely normal, no pneumonia

Protein C, protein S and antithrombin activity levels were all low.  One complicating factor is that after 5 days blood culture was positive for Haemophilus parainfluenza.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I believe I had a delayed reaction to the COVID-19 vaccine that appeared three weeks after my second dose. My lips swelled up rather severely and were burning and very itchy. When I first went to the doctor, we concluded it was a contact dermatitis reaction to some spicy wings I ate. However, the problem persisted for almost five days and started to get worse, which (I'm told) is very unlikely for a food allergy. I ended up going to another primary doctor the next day and she is the one who ended up prescribing an oral steroid and topical steroid. That finally took care of the issue. I would have reported this through VAERS sooner, but was not aware of it. A few days after I started the steroid, I happened to have a dermatology appointment, and my dermatologist said she was aware of delayed reactions tied to vaccines and believed I had angioedema from the COVID-19 vaccine.
LAB_DATA: February 9 - initial doctor visit for swollen lips, February 12 - second doctor visit, prescribed oral and topical steroids, February 16 - dermatologist visit.
OTHER_MEDS: Blisovi FE birth control, women's daily multivitamin
CUR_ILL: No illnesses surrounding the vaccination period

On 4/22/21, approximately 1 hr after the Moderna COVID-19 first vaccination injection, I started to encounter allergic reactions that I used to suffer about 20 years ago. My air intake decreased, and my skin began to become irritated. I formerly had environmental allergies that would reduce my air intake, and the first place I noticed the effects were on my skin and I would become irritable. Physicians told me that when my oxygen levels were low, the body would channel the air to where it was most needed, which is generally not the skin, so my skin would become irritated. When this used to occur, I would respond involuntarily with facial twitches and pulling at my face and hair. Physicians explained that these twitches and pulling actions would draw air to the surface of my skin where I was air depleted. When I took the Moderna injection, this happened again -- I found myself with low air, my face was twitching, and I was pulling on my face to draw air to the area. The result when I was 19 and dealing with allergies is that I would remove small patches of hair from my head or eyebrows or eyelashes, and this would happen almost unconsciously as I tried to stimulate the areas and draw air to the surface of my skin. I did the same thing on 4/22/21, and found later, when looking into a mirror, that I had removed a section of my eyebrow unconsciously. It all comes back to oxygen depletion. A different and more intense event occurred in the night of Friday, 4/23/21, and the early morning of Saturday, 4/24/21. I went to bed at about 11 p.m. or 11:30 p.m. Between that time and approximately 1:30 a.m., I had difficulty sleeping, and I dreamed of pain in my chest. I finally woke up about 1:30 a.m. and found the pain in my chest was real. I was having difficulty breathing deeply. It felt as if  the lower part of my lungs (at least on one side) was solidifying or inaccessible. What I did was begin forcing myself to breathe as deeply as possible. Over a period of 30 minutes or longer, I was able to gradually reclaim the use of the deepest part of my longs. With every forced deep breath, I was able to chip away at the area that felt like it was freezing up. Finally, I felt that I could access the deepest part of my longs and breath normally. The pain and lack of use in my lower lungs were very concerning.
HISTORY: Seasonal Allergies -- effectively treated 23 years ago
PRIOR_VAX: suffered the flu after multiple flu vaccines

Exactly ONE WEEK after I had the 2nd dose of Pfizer, both my arms began to tingle and hurt by 2 pm on a Monday.  Within a few hours, this spread to my entire body; every joint and muscle was in severe pain and discomfort.  I went to bed around 5 pm and had the chills, but no fever.  I continued with this pain for Monday night and could barely sleep.  It continued but not as severe on Tuesday and Wednesday.  By Thursday, I forced myself to take a shower.  By Thursday, the pain in the upper body was gone, but I still had severe pain in both lower legs from the knees down.  It was unbearable if I stood for more than 20 seconds, however, if I lifted each leg and then alternated legs, the pain would go away.  This felt like enormous pressure in my legs and at one point, I thought maybe I had blood clots, but my legs were not red or swollen.  The lower leg pressure finally went away on its own by Sunday, April 25th, 2021.  At no point did I have a fever and I could get some relief by taking Ibuprofen, but not a lot of relief.
LAB_DATA: I stayed at home for the entire 6 days and spent several days in bed.  I did not see a doctor regarding these adverse effects.  I felt it was a bad reaction from the 2nd dose, but why I didn't have the reaction until a week after I had my 2nd dose, I have no idea why?  I looked up adverse effects and it all said within a few days.  I did have some slight pain and general unease the day after my shot, but that lasted 3 hours and then I felt fine.  My husband also had the 2nd dose the same day as me and he only had a 3 hour period the day after the shot where he had aches and a headache and then he was fine.  I thought it was important to report my symptoms and experience to help others who may have had a similar experience.
OTHER_MEDS: Levoxyl for  HypoThyroidism Estradiol Patch/ Testoterone & Projesterone capsules Multi vitamin + vitamin D

On 4/3 patient developed neck pain and headache.  She had reportedly received her second dose of Moderna COVID vaccine within 1 week prior, but exact date unknown. She became acutely confused and reported tingling in her left fingers on 4/9 prompting presentation to Medical Center.  MRI was performed 4/10 reportedly showing an acute focal right corona radiata lacunar infarct. On 4/11 patient became more agitated and 4/12 developed worsening headache and global aphasia. Non-contrast head CT showed multiple areas of subarachnoid hemorrhage bilaterally. MRI brain felt to also have small areas of bilateral diffusion restriction throughout right more than left cerebral hemispheres with concern for leptomeningeal involvement.  She was transferred to another facility for higher level of care on 4/14.  LP on 4/16 with TNC 33 (95% lymphs, 3% monos, 2% macrophages), RBC 1425,  Protein 521, glucose 68. CSF gram stain/culture negative fungal culture and cryptococcal antigen negative, VZV PCR negative, HSV PCR negative, PCR meningitis/encephalitis panel negative, enterovirus culture negative. Serum VZV IgG positive but PCR negative, Lyme and treponemal antibodies negative, HIV Ab negative, ANA/ANCA/Sjogren's antibodies negative. Repeat LP 4/21 with TNC 43 (52% PMN, 35% lymphs, 11% monos, 1% baso, 1% myelos), protein 745, glucose 76). However, given high suspicion for viral encephalitis patient was recommended to complete a 10-14 day course of IV acyclovir by inpatient ID consult service (start date 4/16). She was also treated with empiric steroids. The neurology team is concerned for a possible vasculitis vs reversible cerebral vasoconstriction syndrome as potential etiologies.   Brain biopsy performed 4/23 to help clarify diagnosis, results pending.
HISTORY: 6 months of progressive forgetfulness and confusion, had not had work-up

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 3:30am on Sunday, I woke up due to feeling very cold. My teeth were chattering and regardless of the amount of layers of clothes or blankets added, I could not get warm. Later in the day I checked my temperature and it registered at 100.6 degree Fahrenheit, but I did not feel as cold as I had earlier that morning. I also had what felt like a sinus headache and my whole body felt stiff/achy. There was also some slight nausea that occurred. SYMPTOM_TEXT: At approximately 8:30 AM patient received 2nd dose of Pfizer vaccine in the right arm at the Public Health Center's drive through vaccine clinic. She was accompanied by her husband who was driving her vehicle. At 8:34 AM she notified staff in observation parking area that she felt dizzy, chest pain, and reported wheezing. Two RN's responded at 8:34 AM to observation parking area with emergency kit. Upon arrival, patient verbalized again that she felt dizzy, chest pain and tightness now,  no audible wheezing heard, patient's skin was pale, and her respiratory rate was high. Advised patient to take slow deep breaths and to try to relax and remain calm.  No improvement. At 8:36 AM called 911 for the patient to be evaluated. While one RN was on the phone with 911 operator, patient reports to the second RN throat pain/ tingling, difficulty swallowing, a feeling of a "lump in her throat", continued chest pain and tightness, and states that she feels she cannot breathe in or out well. Per standing order Epinephrine 0.3 mg administered in the right thigh IM. Both RN's remained on scene. No improvement, and patient continued to state it was getting harder to breathe, and that her throat was tingling and she could hardly swallow. At 8:44 AM 0.3 mg Epinephrine administered in the left thigh IM per standing order.  At 8:50 AM EMS arrived. Patient had improvement. Vital signs stable upon arrival per EMS. Breathing difficulty improved upon EMS arrival.  No further difficulty swallowing reported. Chest pain reported to be improved as well. 8:55 AM EMS transported patient to local hospital.  Attempted to contact the patient on 04-26-2021 to determine outcome of event. Phone went to voicemail. Voice message left.
LAB_DATA: Vital signs taken upon arrival 04-23-2021 @ 8:50 AM by EMS.
HISTORY: Seizure disorder reported by husband. No other conditions reported.
ALLERGIES: Shellfish and aspirin. Patient and husband are unsure of other allergies at time of reaction. States that they typically have a list, but did not bring it to the vaccine clinic on 04-23-2021. States that there are "a few more". Patient carries epi pen due to shellfish allergy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Before I start, I've really tried documenting this to you earlier and it kept timing out on me. Hopefully the third time is a charm! On Saturday, April 17th at approximately 11:55 am, (45 mins after my shot) I started experiencing partial paralysis to the left side of my face. My cheek bone started to go numb, within the hour, after a weird tingling sensation, it went from my cheek bone down towards my jaw (all becoming numb). This lasted all weekend. I used cold compresses for a little bit at a time just to make the heat coming off of that side feel a little better as my face was flushed. On Monday, April 19th, my lower cheek started to not be so numb. The tingling sensation would come and go from my eye brawl, then the side of my mouth/lip area. I developed a headache that Monday evening. Tuesday morning, my headache was gone. This tingling sensation and partial numbing would last through Wednesday, April 21st. That day, I called my doctor's office and told them about my reaction and to see if they could do some blood work or something. They said that I needed to go to the ER at a hospital for help and to get it documented. Out of all weeks for me to have a side effect, this busy mom had too much going on to schedule an ER visit. My daughter is going into high school and she had auditions and clinics where I had made the choice to figure out I will try to go there on another day. By Thursday, April 22nd, my cheek bone started to become un-numb. The affected side started to feel like the other side of my face. During this entire time, I didn't take any medicine. By Friday, April 23rd, I felt much better. I have more control of my face muscles and I feel like this might be something that was just temporary, but I told myself that if it comes back in any way, I will go to the ER regardless of what is going on in my life. It was a scary thing and now as I look at my card, it reads that the second shot is May 8th at 11:15. I am really scared to get that because who knows what will come from it and I wouldn't want to get anything permanent. I know with traveling, some countries are making it mandatory to be vaccinated. So does this mean that I will not be able to travel if I don't get that second shot. I have no idea what to do with this appointment. Any advice would be great! As of today, April 26th, I feel 95% better on my left side of my face but if I sleep on it for too long, it tends to feel heated at my cheek bone. Aside from that I'm much better. Now onto the second side effect, my left arm muscle was in excruciating pain and I could not lift my arm for two days. It effected my elbow to my shoulder. After Monday, April 19th, my arm started to get better every day. This was the arm that I got my shot in. Today, April 26th, is the first day it seems back to normal. I know you can have a sore arm with this shot, but this was much more than a sore arm. My left side of my face, my left arm, and a headache were the only abnormal events that took place after my first Covid shot. I am thankful to be feeling much better, but will continue to monitor the situation of my face as that is what is most concerning about this vaccination.
LAB_DATA: N/A. The next question I'm going to put no as I'm 95% better but still have a tiny bit of discomfort at my cheek bone every now and then.

Later on 3/4/21 brain fog was significantly impacting me and it was hard to complete sentences and communicate effectively.  From 3/2/21 to 3/ 3/7/21 I experienced brain fog, fatigue, dizziness, and chills (no fever).  I was fine on 3/8/21.  All 4 side effects came back on 3/24/21.  I was having chills, no fever, early in the day then led a meeting in the early afternoon and could barely finish my briefing.  I was having issues with fatigue, some dizziness, and brain fog. I also took Meclizine with limited impacts.  Also took a prednisone pack that took the edge off.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 24 hours after my second covid vaccine I came down with a very intense headache like many; it was deep in my eye sockets, my ears, jaw, and teeth, a radiating, pulsating type pain. By the next morning I was better. That night, April 11, I was awoken in the middle of the night with the same kind of pulsing pain in my teeth. It became progressively worse over the next two weeks to the point where I could not rest my top and bottom teeth together or eat any kind of solid food. By Monday April 19, I went to an urgent care clinic to see if there was anything wrong with my sinuses, nothing (the doctor said at the time that if it wasn't my teeth that I should see an ENT). At this point I was taking 800 milligrams of ibuprofen every 4 hours and slathering my teeth with orajel numbing gel. By 4/21 I was able to get an emergency appointment with my dentist- she did x-rays and saw nothing. She said if the pain continued for another 2 weeks she would send me to a root canal specialist. She also encouraged me to wear a mouth guard to help. By Friday, my 2 weeks after my 2 shot, I was able to get through the day without medication. Today is Monday 4/26 and while I am almost fully better, the teeth are still sore and I can only eat mushy solid foods.
LAB_DATA: I have a May 5 appointment to see an ENT. Neurology appointments were not available until June.

Patient became unconscious the evening of 4/14/21.  This event occurred five days after his second Covid vaccination. Patient had just gotten up from a living room chair and was walking over to the stairs to go to the second floor when he became rigid, lost consciousness and fell backward.  911 was called by his girlfriend.  He was unconscious for a couple of minutes.  When EMT's arrived he was conscious but very groggy.  His blood pressure was 250/157.  He knew his name and year and SSN but did not correctly answer several other questions.  He was taken to ER.  After numerous tests over the course of several days, he was diagnosed as having a stroke.    In the ER, they performed CAT scans, EKG, blood work, urine test and chest xray.  Blood pressure remained high.  Complained of headaches.  Patient was also having trouble voiding urine in the ER so a foley catheter was inserted.  He was admitted to the hospital.  After admission, an MRI, echocardiogram and EEG were performed.  The MRI showed three small blood vessels had burst in his brain.  Echocardiogram showed functions were normal.  The EEG showed some slowing but no signs of seizure.  The conclusion was a stroke.  Physical and occupational therapy examined patient.  No need for further therapy.  Blood pressure remains slightly elevated but he does not appear at this time to have lost any physical or mental functions.  Patient does NOT have a history of high blood pressure or heart issues.  Tests showed his heart was functioning properly.  Per his family doctor, his BP ran approximately 124/64 when tested during the previous 12 months.

CT-C Scan - Spine/Head - 04/14/21 - no acute abnormalities in the head or cervical spine  CT-A Scan - chest/abdomen/pelvis was concerning for occlusion of the proximal right SFA, moderate distention of the urinary bladder. Urine Analysis - 04/14/21 - no pyuria  Chest xray - 04/14/21 - no acute cardiopulmonary process  2D Echocardiogram - 04/15/21 - no issues  MRI Brain Scan - 04/16/21 - tiny focus of acute ischemia involving the left medial temporal lobe medial temporal lobe.
